---
# DESIGN.md template for apps/{APP_SLUG}/DESIGN.md or
# workspace/businesses/{BIZ}/L2-tactical/design/DESIGN.md
#
# Conforms to Google DESIGN.md spec (alpha) + Sinkra-Hub `## Implementation` extension.
# Validate with: npx @google/design.md lint DESIGN.md
#
# Placeholders (replace before commit):
#   {DS_NAME}            — human-readable DS name (e.g. "Redpine DS")
#   {ONE_LINE_SUMMARY}   — one-sentence brand positioning
#   {APP_OR_BUSINESS}    — "app" or "business"
#   {SOT_PATH}           — path to tokens source (e.g. src/design-system/tokens.json)
#   {STACK_FRAMEWORK}    — Next.js 16 / Vite 5 / SvelteKit / etc.
#   {TAILWIND_VERSION}   — 3.x / 4.x
#   {TAILWIND_CONFIG}    — tailwind.config.ts / src/app/globals.css (@theme inline)
#   {SHADCN_BASE_COLOR}  — slate / stone / gray / zinc / neutral
#   {REGEN_CMD}          — e.g. npm run build:tokens
#
# Each color/typography/component entry is a placeholder to be filled from real
# token sources. Consumer behavior: unknown tokens are accepted with a warning;
# duplicate section headings are rejected; missing sections are permitted.

version: alpha
name: {DS_NAME}
description: >
  {ONE_LINE_SUMMARY}. Canonical token source: {SOT_PATH}. This is the
  authoritative DS artifact for {APP_OR_BUSINESS}; code generation reads this
  file first.

colors:
  # Primary palette (REQUIRED slots — fill from brand source)
  primary: "#000000"              # REPLACE — signature accent hex
  secondary: "#000000"             # REPLACE — body text / dark surface
  tertiary: "#000000"              # REPLACE — structural neutral
  neutral: "#FFFFFF"               # REPLACE — page background
  surface: "#FFFFFF"               # REPLACE — elevated card surface
  on-primary: "#FFFFFF"            # REPLACE — fg on primary
  on-secondary: "#FFFFFF"          # REPLACE — fg on secondary
  on-surface: "#000000"            # REPLACE — fg on surface

  # Extended palette (add named tokens as the brand requires — valid hex values
  # are accepted by the linter with a warning if unreferenced by any component)

  # Semantic feedback (recommend triplets: default / deep / wash for AA-safe pairs)
  success: "#2E6F55"
  success-deep: "#1E4A39"
  success-wash: "#E3EFE9"
  warning: "#A66A1F"
  warning-deep: "#6B4312"
  warning-wash: "#F8EEDD"
  info: "#2A4E6E"
  info-deep: "#17304A"
  info-wash: "#E0E9F0"
  danger: "#B43232"
  danger-deep: "#892323"
  danger-wash: "#F8EBEB"

typography:
  # Minimum set: at least one display, one body, one label/eyebrow
  h1:
    fontFamily: system-ui          # REPLACE with brand face
    fontSize: 40px
    fontWeight: 600
    lineHeight: 1.1
    letterSpacing: -0.015em
  body:
    fontFamily: system-ui          # REPLACE with brand face
    fontSize: 16px
    fontWeight: 400
    lineHeight: 1.5
    letterSpacing: 0em
  caption:
    fontFamily: system-ui
    fontSize: 13px
    fontWeight: 400
    lineHeight: 1.4
    letterSpacing: 0em
  eyebrow:
    fontFamily: system-ui
    fontSize: 12px
    fontWeight: 500
    lineHeight: 1.2
    letterSpacing: 0.10em
  mono:
    fontFamily: ui-monospace
    fontSize: 14px
    fontWeight: 400
    lineHeight: 1.5
    letterSpacing: 0em

spacing:
  "0": 0px
  "1": 4px
  "2": 8px
  "3": 12px
  "4": 16px
  "6": 24px
  "8": 32px
  "10": 40px
  "12": 48px
  "16": 64px
  "24": 96px
  "32": 128px

rounded:
  none: 0px
  sm: 4px
  md: 8px
  lg: 12px
  full: 9999px

components:
  # Minimum surface set — expand to cover the real component inventory
  button-primary:
    backgroundColor: "{colors.primary}"
    textColor: "{colors.on-primary}"
    typography: "{typography.body}"
    rounded: "{rounded.md}"
    padding: 12px
  button-secondary:
    backgroundColor: "{colors.surface}"
    textColor: "{colors.secondary}"
    typography: "{typography.body}"
    rounded: "{rounded.md}"
    padding: 12px
  button-ghost:
    backgroundColor: "transparent"
    textColor: "{colors.primary}"
    typography: "{typography.body}"
    rounded: "{rounded.md}"
    padding: 8px
  button-destructive:
    backgroundColor: "{colors.danger-deep}"
    textColor: "{colors.on-primary}"
    typography: "{typography.body}"
    rounded: "{rounded.md}"
    padding: 12px

  card:
    backgroundColor: "{colors.surface}"
    textColor: "{colors.on-surface}"
    rounded: "{rounded.md}"
    padding: 24px

  input:
    backgroundColor: "{colors.surface}"
    textColor: "{colors.on-surface}"
    typography: "{typography.body}"
    rounded: "{rounded.sm}"
    padding: 12px
  input-invalid:
    backgroundColor: "{colors.surface}"
    textColor: "{colors.danger-deep}"

  alert-info:
    backgroundColor: "{colors.info-wash}"
    textColor: "{colors.info-deep}"
    rounded: "{rounded.md}"
    padding: 16px
  alert-success:
    backgroundColor: "{colors.success-wash}"
    textColor: "{colors.success-deep}"
    rounded: "{rounded.md}"
    padding: 16px
  alert-warning:
    backgroundColor: "{colors.warning-wash}"
    textColor: "{colors.warning-deep}"
    rounded: "{rounded.md}"
    padding: 16px
  alert-danger:
    backgroundColor: "{colors.danger-wash}"
    textColor: "{colors.danger-deep}"
    rounded: "{rounded.md}"
    padding: 16px

  badge-default:
    backgroundColor: "{colors.tertiary}"
    textColor: "{colors.on-surface}"
    typography: "{typography.caption}"
    rounded: "{rounded.full}"
    padding: 4px
---

# {DS_NAME}

## Overview

Replace this paragraph with the brand positioning in two or three sentences. Describe tone, target audience, and the emotional response the UI should evoke. This is the foundational context for any stylistic decision when a specific rule or token isn't explicitly defined.

## Colors

Describe the color strategy. For each primary slot:
- **Primary (#______):** what it is, what it signals, where it's allowed.
- **Secondary (#______):** role in the hierarchy.
- **Tertiary (#______):** structural use.
- **Neutral (#______):** canvas / page surface.

Describe ramps (ink ramp, neutral ramp, accent ramps) and the feedback triplet convention. State hard rules like "exactly one primary action per screen" or "no gradient fills of the signature."

## Typography

Describe the type strategy. Faces, weights, and the register of each (display / body / meta). State the scale and the clamps (if fluid). State the discipline — never mix more than N weights per screen, cap measure at X px, etc.

## Layout

Describe the grid system (columns, gutters, max content width), spacing scale, container strategy, and any signature layout idioms (palette attributes, grid overlays, editorial spreads).

## Elevation & Depth

Describe how visual hierarchy is conveyed. Shadows or hairlines? Tonal layers? Glassmorphism? What's allowed, what's forbidden, what's reserved for transient surfaces only.

## Shapes

Describe the radius strategy, which radii pair with which surfaces, and what's forbidden. Icon system (family + stroke + sizing convention). Emoji policy.

## Components

Describe each component family in prose — variants, states, accessibility defaults, typography per slot. Reference `currentColor` inheritance and semantic token discipline (e.g., "components consume Tailwind utilities, utilities reference semantic vars, semantic vars alias primitives").

## Do's and Don'ts

**Do:**
- Do use [primary] for exactly one action per screen
- Do cap body text at [measure]
- Do use hairlines for separation; shadows only for transient surfaces
- Do maintain WCAG AA contrast using the wash + deep pair for tinted alerts

**Don't:**
- Don't use emoji
- Don't mix rounded and sharp corners in the same composition
- Don't gradient-fill the signature
- Don't let color alone carry semantic meaning

## Implementation

**Stack:** {STACK_FRAMEWORK}

**Token source of truth:** `{SOT_PATH}`
**Regenerate:** `{REGEN_CMD}` (if applicable)

**Tailwind config:** `{TAILWIND_CONFIG}` (version {TAILWIND_VERSION})

**shadcn config:** `components.json`
- baseColor: {SHADCN_BASE_COLOR}
- cssVariables: true
- prefix: "" (no utility prefix)
- aliases: `@/components`, `@/components/ui`, `@/lib/utils`

**Token → utility mapping (canonical layers):**

| DESIGN.md token | Primitive CSS var | Semantic CSS var | Tailwind utility |
|---|---|---|---|
| primary | `--[brand-prefix]-primary` | `--primary` | `bg-primary` / `text-primary` |
| surface | `--[brand-prefix]-surface` | `--background` / `--card` | `bg-background` / `bg-card` |
| secondary | `--[brand-prefix]-ink` | `--foreground` | `text-foreground` |
| tertiary | `--[brand-prefix]-border` | `--border` | `border-border` |

**Layer discipline:**

1. **Layer 1 — Primitives.** Raw token values (`--rp-red`, `--rp-ink`). Defined from DESIGN.md `colors:` block.
2. **Layer 2 — Semantic aliases.** Role-based vars (`--bg`, `--fg`, `--accent`). Every component consumes these, never primitives directly.
3. **Layer 3 — Tailwind utilities / shadcn slots.** `bg-primary`, `text-foreground`, `border-border`. Components reference Layer 3; never skip to Layer 1.

**Component source:** `src/components/ui/*.tsx` (or app equivalent). Kebab-case filenames, PascalCase exports.

**Regenerate artifacts:** After any edit to this DESIGN.md, run `{REGEN_CMD}` (if applicable) and confirm `npx @google/design.md lint DESIGN.md` reports 0 errors.
